{{Sangam literature}}
'''Māngudi Maruthanār''' ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: மாங்குடி மருதனார்), also known as Mānkudi Kilār ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: மாங்குடி கிழார்), Madhurai Kānchi Pulavar ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: மதுரை காஞ்சி புலவர்), and Kānchi Pulavanār ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: காஞ்சிப்புலவனார்), was a poet of the [[Sangam period]], to whom 13 verses of the Sangam literature have been attributed, including verse 24 of the [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]]. He was the author of [[Madurai Kaanchi]] of the [[Pathupattu]] (the Ten Idylls).<ref name="Vedanayagam_Urai">{{cite book | last = Vedanayagam | first = Rama | author-link = | title = திருவள்ளுவ மாலை மூலமும் எளிய உரை விளக்கமும் [Tiruvalluva Maalai: Moolamum Eliya Urai Vilakkamum] | publisher = Manimekalai Prasuram | series = | volume = | edition = 1 | date = 2017 | location = Chennai | pages =38–39 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Biography== Mangudi Marudhanar hailed from the town of Mangudi and belonged to the Vellan caste.<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_2">{{cite book | last = Kowmareeshwari (Ed.) | first = S. | author-link = | title = [Kurunthogai, Paripaadal, Kalithogai] | publisher = Saradha Pathippagam | series = Sanga Ilakkiyam | volume = 2 | edition = 1 | date = August 2012 | location = Chennai | pages = 447 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Contribution to the Sangam literature== Mangudi Marudhanar wrote the [[Madurai Kaanchi]] literature of the [[Pathupattu]] (the Ten Idylls). Besides he has written 13 Sangam verses, including 3 in [[Kurunthogai]], 2 in [[Natrinai]], 6 in [[Purananuru]], 1 in [[Agananuru]], and 1 in [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_2"/>
