The '''Nihilist Faction''' ({{lang-el|Φράξια Μηδενιστών|translit=Fraxia Midheniston}}) was a [[Nihilist movement|Nihilist]] [[Anarchism|Anarchist]] organization in Greece, which claimed responsibility for a 28 May 1996 bombing of [[IBM]] offices in [[Athens]]. The attack caused extensive structural damage but no injuries.
